## 📊🎭 Example Scenarios

### 🔵 Example 1 — Standard Weekday Due Date
```
💰 Initial Balance : 800,000
💳 Payment Amount  : 100,000
📅 Payment Date    : March 14, 2026 (Saturday)
🥈 Match Tier      : 3%  (100K ≤ x < 500K)

🎁 Incentive       = 100,000 × 0.03 = 3,000
💵 New Balance     = 800,000 − (100,000 + 3,000) = 697,000
📅 Due Date        = March 14 + 90 days = June 12, 2026 ✅ (Friday — no adjustment)
```

### 🟠 Example 2 — Weekend Due Date Adjustment
```
💰 Initial Balance : 800,000
💳 Payment Amount  : 575,000
📅 Payment Date    : April 5, 2026 (Sunday)
🥇 Match Tier      : 5%  (x ≥ 500K)

🎁 Incentive       = 575,000 × 0.05 = 28,750
💵 New Balance     = 800,000 − (575,000 + 28,750) = 196,250
📅 Due Date        = April 5 + 90 days = July 4, 2026 (Saturday ➡️ adjusted to July 6, 2026 ✅ Monday)
```

### 🟡 Example 3 — Low Tier
```
💰 Initial Balance : 200,000
💳 Payment Amount  : 50,000
📅 Payment Date    : March 13, 2026
🥉 Match Tier      : 1%  (0 < x < 100K)

🎁 Incentive       = 50,000 × 0.01 = 500
💵 New Balance     = 200,000 − (50,000 + 500) = 149,500
📅 Due Date        = March 13 + 90 days = June 11, 2026 ✅ (Thursday — no adjustment)
```

---

## 🔍🛠️ Edge Cases Handled

| Edge Case ⚠️                       | Handling 🛡️                                             |
|-----------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
| `paymentAmount = 0` 🚫             | ❌ Rejected — `@DecimalMin("0.01")` validation ✅       |
| `paymentAmount < 0` ➖              | ❌ Rejected — validation 🛡️                            |
| `paymentAmount > currentBalance` ⬆️ | ❌ Rejected — service-level check 🔍                  |
| `paymentAmount = 99,999.99` 🟡     | ✅ 1% tier 🥉 (just below 100K boundary)               |
| `paymentAmount = 100,000.00` 🟠    | ✅ 3% tier 🥈 (exactly at boundary)                    |
| `paymentAmount = 499,999.99` 🟠    | ✅ 3% tier 🥈 (just below 500K boundary)               |
| `paymentAmount = 500,000.00` 🟢    | ✅ 5% tier 🥇 (exactly at boundary)                    |
| Due date on Saturday 📅            | ✅ Moved to Monday ➡️ (+2 days)                        |
| Due date on Sunday 📅              | ✅ Moved to Monday ➡️ (+1 day)                         |
| Student not found 👤               | ❌ `404 NotFoundException` 🚫                           |
| Account not found 💰               | ❌ `404 NotFoundException` 🚫                           |
| Stripe payment fails 💳            | ❌ `400 BadRequestException` — balance not updated 🔒  |
| Duplicate student number 🔢        | ❌ `400 BadRequestException` 🚫                         |
| Invalid JWT token 🔑               | ❌ `401 Unauthorized` 🚨                                |
| Insufficient role 🛡️              | ❌ `403 Forbidden` 🚫                                   |
| Profile picture > 5MB 📸           | ❌ `400 BadRequestException` ⚠️                         |
| Invalid image format 🖼️           | ❌ Only JPEG, PNG, WEBP allowed ✅                      |

---

## 💭🧠 Assumptions & Trade-offs

### 📌 Assumptions
1. 💱 **Currency**: The system accepts any valid ISO 4217 currency code. Stripe handles conversion.
2. ⚠️ **Balance cannot go negative**: A payment exceeding the current balance is rejected.
3. 📅 **Payment date**: Defaults to the current system date if not provided by the caller.
4. 📊 **Incentive tiers**: Applied on the raw `paymentAmount`, not on the total deduction.
5. 🗑️ **Soft deletes**: Student profiles are never hard deleted — `isDeleted` flag is used.
6. 🌱 **Seeded users**: On startup, the `SeederConfig` creates one user per role if they don't exist.

### ⚖️ Trade-offs
| Decision 🔧                          | Rationale 💡                                                 |
|----------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| `BigDecimal` over `double` 🔢     | Eliminates floating-point rounding errors in money calculations 💰 |
| Soft delete for student profiles 🗑️ | Preserves historical payment data and audit trails 📋       |
| Separate `StudentAccount` entity 🏦 | Decouples financial data from profile data — easier to extend 🔧 |
| `JpaSpecificationExecutor` 🔍     | Replaces 20+ query methods with a single dynamic `findAll(spec, pageable)` ⚡ |
| `disableBuilder = true` in MapStruct 🗺️ | Avoids Lombok `@Builder` vs MapStruct naming conflicts for `boolean isX` fields 🛡️ |
| Redis for token blacklisting 🔴   | Stateless JWT + server-side invalidation on logout 🚪        |
| Firebase credentials from env vars 🔥 | Avoids committing service account JSON to version control 🔐 |
| `cloudinary-http5` over `cloudinary-core` ☁️ | `core` alone has no HTTP adapter and fails on startup 🚫 |

---

## 📁🗂️ Project Structure

```
studentFeeOneTimePayment/ 📦
├── src/ 📂
│   ├── main/ 🚀
│   │   ├── java/com/leedTech/studentFeeOneTimePayment/
│   │   │   ├── config/ ⚙️
│   │   │   │   ├── cloudinaryConfig/       # ☁️ Cloudinary bean
